  "text": "Both KM and DM can model the effect of glass width using this formalism. The issue that divides the two models is how they determine the rate at which the triangle stretches toward the rim. KM depends on spatial relations to regulate the rate of stretching. One correct kinematic solution, shown in panel c, ensures that side A and the horizon maintain a constant angle during rotation. Other solutions, varying in levels of absolute accuracy, can be found by aligning different spatial features and angles within the system [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
